# Approach 1 Using recursion(Brute force)

# Hints 
- Use recursion 
- Start from Destination grid[n][m] 
- Each time check :- 
    - If we reach source(i.e. n == 0 && m == 0) return grid[0][0]
    - Else if index is not valid return Integer.MAX_VALUE
    - Else return cost of current node(grid[n][m]) sum with mininum of cost to reach (n-1, m) and (n, m-1).

# Note 
- It will give Time Limit Exceeded as time is 2^n

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(2^(n*m))

# Code 
```
class Solution {
    public int minPathSum(int[][] grid) {
        return minPathSum(grid, grid.length-1, grid[0].length-1);
    }
    private int minPathSum(int[][] grid, int n, int m){
        if(n == 0 && m == 0) return grid[n][m];
        if(n < 0 || m < 0) return Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        return grid[n][m] + Math.min(minPathSum(grid, n-1, m), minPathSum(grid, n, m-1));
    }
}
```

