solutions.content:
Simple DP solution in O(n^2)

Step 1: Initialize a dp array
Step 2: Fill the 0th row and 0th column of dp array where, the value at any position of row or column is the sum of all the elements from 0 to that index in the grid vector.
Step 3: Using two for loops iterate the whole dp array except the 0th row and col as we have already filled them in Step 2.
Step 4: The value of the dp[ i ][ j ] will be the value of grid[ i ][ j ] + min(dp[ i-1 ][ j ], dp[ i ][ j-1 ]) i.e.
the value will be sum of the current value at grid, plus the minimum of the element at the top or element at the left side of the current element in the array.
Step 5: At the end return the value of the dp[ row-1 ][ col-1 ] i.e the last element of the matrix dp.


```
class Solution {
public:
    int minPathSum(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {


        int row = grid.size();
        int col = grid[0].size();

		// Step 1: Initialize a dp array

        int dp[row][col];

		// Step 2: Fill the 0th row and 0th column of dp array where, the value at any position of row or
		// column is the sum of all the elements from 0 to that index in the grid vector.

        dp[0][0]=grid[0][0];
        for(int i=1;i<col;i++)
            dp[0][i] = dp[0][i-1]+grid[0][i];
        for(int i=1;i<row;i++)
            dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0]+grid[i][0];

		// Step 3: Using two for loops iterate the whole dp array except the 0th row and col as we have already 
		// filled them in Step 2.

        for(int i=1;i<grid.size();i++){
            for(int j=1;j<grid[0].size();j++){

			// Step 4: The value of the dp[ i ][ j ] will be the value of grid[ i ][ j ] + min(dp[ i-1 ][ j ], dp[ i ][ j-1 ]) i.e.
			// the value will be sum of the current value at grid plus the minimum of the element at the top or 
			// element at the left side of the current element in the array.

                dp[i][j] = min(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1])+grid[i][j];
            }
        }

		// Step 5: At the end return the value of the dp[ row-1 ][ col-1 ] i.e the last element of the matrix dp.

        return dp[row-1][col-1];

    }
};
```

