# Intuition
To find minimum path sum we need result of our previous choices that we took, so this gives us intution of storing previous data and hence we choose DP
Considering testcase 1
Input: grid = [[1,3,1],[1,5,1],[4,2,1]]
Output: 7

# Approach
***Beginner -> Space O(n^2)***

1) Begin by taking same size 2D and fill the first element from grid[0][0] to our new matrix dp[][];
2) Prefill first row and first column, because 

- ROW
We can reach row 0 elements from only side i.e grid[0][0] will contribute to grid[0][1]  and so on
intially grid : 1 --> 3 ---> 1
so first row will look like 
after operation dp: 1 --> 4 --> 5

- COL
We can reach row 0 elements only from top as left indexes are out of bound
grid --after operation-->  dp
1  ---->  1
5  ---->  6
1  ---->  7

3) Now for any other element will is not part of corner case, we can reach from top or from same row left side so 
dp[i][j] = Math.min(element from top, element from side) + current value
dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i][j-1], dp[i-1][j])

and we return the last element of dp[n][n] which is the answer

---


*Space O(n)*
We can also solve the problem by using a 1D array, the array will always store the upper row values ( i.e the values that we fetch via dp[i-1][j]).
So initially we will prefill it with 1 row same as in 2nd step row part.

Min path of any element is
dp[j] = elements values will be added + min of ( top, side)
- top row data is already in the dp array and side we can calculate via dp[j-1]
dp[j]=  grid[i][j] +Math.min(dp[j], dp[j-1])+


---


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n^2) Since we visit all element of the matrix.

# Code Space O(n^2)
```
class Solution {
    public int minPathSum(int[][] grid) {
        if(grid==null || grid.length==0 )
            return 0;
        int row = grid.length;
        int col = grid[0].length;

        /* prefilling the first row and first column */
        for(int i=1;i<col;i++)
            grid[0][i]+=grid[0][i-1];

        for(int i=1;i<row;i++)
            grid[i][0]+=grid[i-1][0];

        for(int i=1;i<row;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<col;j++){
                grid[i][j]+=Math.min(grid[i][j-1], grid[i-1][j]);
            }
        }
        return grid[row-1][col-1];
    }
}
```

# Code Space O(n)
```
class Solution {
    public int minPathSum(int[][] grid) {
        int row= grid.length;
        int col= grid[0].length;
        int [] dp = new int[col];

        dp[0]= grid[0][0];

        for(int i=1; i<col;i++)
            dp[i]=dp[i-1] + grid[0][i];

        for(int i=1; i<row; i++){
            for(int j=0; j<col; j++){
                if(j>0){
                    dp[j]=Math.min(dp[j], dp[j-1])+ grid[i][j];
                }else{
                    dp[j]+=grid[i][j];
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[col-1];

    }
}
```
